# Push Critical Scaffold After Major Milestones

After every major completion point on this project, push the critical app scaffold and project artifacts to:

`https://github.com/cassidythilton/dbais-2026-revenue-command-center`

Major completion points include:

- Domo app scaffold/publish workflow changes (`pattern4-agent-portal/`, `dist/`, `manifest.json`, `thumbnail.png`, `public/`, `src/`).
- Code Engine package source/contract changes, excluding real secrets/tokens.
- Databricks/Genie/ML/Lakebase integration assets and scripts.
- Scope, shaping, roadmap, validation, and tracker docs.
- Any released/demo-ready state that would be costly to reconstruct.

Before pushing:

- Run `git status` and review changed files.
- Do not commit or push secrets, tokens, local auth files, or generated files that contain credentials.
- Keep `databricks token` and any real Code Engine token-bearing payloads out of git.
- Use normal git safety: no force push, no destructive reset/checkout, and only commit when the user has explicitly requested it or when this rule applies after a major completion point.
- Prefer concise milestone commit messages focused on the outcome.

If the remote is not configured, add/verify it only after checking current remotes and repository state.
